            "product_text_content_1": "<p>Rogue Fitness is the leading first-class manufacturer of strength and conditioning equipment, including barbells, power racks, all-in-one machines, and accessories. The company is the official equipment supplier of the cross training games, weightlifting, the Arnold Strongman Classic games, as well as the World’s Strongest Man competitions. Rogue is dedicated to serve the needs of serious athletes of every fitness level.</p><p>The Rogue lever belt is a decent choice for any powerlifter who prefers vigorous training sessions. Due to the lever system, you can easily get in and out quickly between lifts. However, it won't be the best choice for Olympic lifters, because the lever mechanism itself can hinder the pulling motion for snatches and clean & jerks.</p><p>Being made of genuine sole leather, this garment is the best lever belt on the list. It features a black suede liner, an embossed Rogue logo, and patented lock-in matte-black lever from nickel-plated steel that replaces a traditional buckle.</p><p>With beveled edges, the belt won't slip or move while you're training by providing strong back support and stability through heavy lifts. You'll find a wide range of sizes, although the manufacturer informs that these belts tend to be one size larger than most <a href=\"https://www.roguefitness.com/rogue-branded-black-leather-13mm-4-inch-lever-belt/?a_aid=62ff8b7e519eb\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.roguefitness.com/rogue-branded-black-leather-13mm-4-inch-lever-belt/?a_aid=62ff8b7e519eb\">weight belts</a> with a lever. So, if your size is medium, you'd better select a small size option.</p>",
            "product_review_image": "shopify://shop_images/training-lever-belt-rogue-insta.jpg",
            "half_width_review_image": true,
            "product_review_image_caption": "<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Cnz-0skMKVW/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Cnz-0skMKVW/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\">@roguefitness</a></p>",
            "product_text_content_2": "<p>The weight of the lever belt is around 3 lb and its width is 4\". The leather is 13\" in thickness and is vegetable-tanned. What's important, the belt is IPF-approved, so you can wear it at the official IPF competitions. The edges are beveled for more comfort, while the inner side is made so that it won't slip as it is roughened up pretty well.</p><p>The leather pieces are sewn together with a single stitching. The lever itself can be customized to any lifter, as it can be screwed in place. Six screws need to be fixed to make the belt work.</p><p>You'll benefit from wearing this big and sturdy belt if you prefer lifting heavy weights often. When it is properly adjusted, you get great equipment suitable for advanced powerlifters and those who prefer to work with serious weights.</p>",
            "product_pros": "<ul><li>Quality material and construction with solid buckle</li><li>Feels rock solid when bracing</li><li>Shapes into your body well while still giving great support</li><li>The break in period was minimal at most</li></ul>",
            "product_cons": "<ul><li>Holes are too far apart and are not spaced right, so it won’t latch well</li><li>Digs into ribs or hips</li></ul>"
          }
